gomodel:SYNGO_2626  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Results section: \"Synaptic activity increases the surface expression of GLUT3\"\n\n-Literal: \"Immunostaining of hippocampal neurons with antibodies against the C-terminal domain of GLUT3 (redabel; rhodamine) and synaptophysin (green label; fluorescein) showed GLUT3 staining in dendrites and in the cell body (Fig. 1C); synaptophysin staining was noted in presynaptic nerve terminals (Fig. 1D). Merged images show the juxtaposition of synaptophysin and GLUT3 punctae (Fig. 1E), which suggests a synaptic location of GLUT3.\"\n\n22/2/2018 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Materials and methods section: \"Cell culture\"\n\n-Literal: \"p.1991: \"Cultured embryonic day (E) 18 rat cortical and hippocampal neurons were prepared as described previously...\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099699 replaced by GO:0097060" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6893-6177" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5265-6306" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2626" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

